## The Onboarding Pipeline

The pipeline is a dependency chain. Each step unlocks the next.
Steps 1 and 2 run in parallel. Nothing technical starts before Step 2 closes.

```
STEP 1 — ENVIRONMENT INTAKE
Who:      Client
Output:   ClientInfo watchlist, EnvironmentProfile doc
Unlocks:  Full picture of who we are working with —
          environment, crown jewels, compliance, licensing,
          Defender XDR connector status
Have it:  YES — intake package ready (see Deliverables)

STEP 2 — LIGHTHOUSE DELEGATION
Who:      End client's tenant admin (cannot be proxied —
          Azure does not allow re-delegation)
Output:   Platform team has access to the workspace
Unlocks:  Everything technical. This is the critical path.
Have it:  YES — Lighthouse guidance doc ready

STEP 3 — AUDIT WORKBOOK RUN
Who:      Platform team
Process:  KQL to find active tables → PowerShell to pull
          schemas and detections → Python to parse into
          spreadsheet and per-table files → AI analysis
          per table (category, subcategory, connector,
          description, sub-sources, detection logic)
Output:   Active table inventory, schema map,
          existing detection inventory,
          table→detection→watchlist mapping
Unlocks:  You know what is actually in the workspace
Have it:  YES — audit process exists

STEP 4 — BASELINE CHECKLIST
Who:      Platform team (internal)
Output:   Gap report — UEBA enabled, auditing on,
          MMA remnants, DCR coverage, support plan,
          Defender XDR connector configured,
          commitment tier optimized, daily cap set
Unlocks:  Phase 1 findings report — first wow deliverable
Have it:  NOT YET — Fable 5 job

STEP 5 — DATA SOURCE INTAKE
Who:      Collaborative — platform team pre-populates
          from Step 3 audit output, client confirms
          and fills gaps only they know
Fields:   Table, Multi, Data Source, Category,
          Source Category, Data Connector, DCR, DCE,
          Transport, Description, Dependencies,
          Health Mon, Sec Detections, Retention,
          Vetted, Notes, API Key Expiry,
          Cribl/Forwarder, Load Balancer,
          Custom Parser, Forwarder Owner
Output:   DataSources watchlist — master source of
          truth for the environment
Unlocks:  Detection team knows what to deploy.
          Silent-log watchlist gets built.
Have it:  NOT YET — collaborative template to build

STEP 6 — CRITICAL ASSET + WATCHLIST INTAKE
Who:      Dedicated working session with client
Output:   Unified critical watchlist
          (source, type, threshold, severity,
          owner, escalation path)
          Silent-log detection scope defined
Unlocks:  Silent-log detections, priority alerting,
          HA edge case handling
Have it:  NOT YET — Fable 5 job
Note:     Telegraph tomorrow: "one of our early sessions
          will map your most critical sources and assets —
          that drives how we tune alerting specifically
          for your environment"

STEP 7 — DETECTION DEPLOYMENT
Who:      Detection team
Input:    DataSources watchlist (Step 5),
          Critical asset watchlist (Step 6)
Output:   Managed detections pushed to environment,
          keep/kill/replace decision on existing rules
Unlocks:  Automation rules live, logic app wired,
          incidents flowing to ServiceNow

STEP 8 — INTEGRATION + VALIDATION
Who:      Platform team
Output:   End-to-end test fire confirmed,
          ServiceNow ticket flow verified,
          client portal access live,
          silent-log detections armed and tested
Unlocks:  Go-live and hypercare

STEP 9 — AUDITDECK REVIEW (The Payoff)
Who:      Platform team presents, client receives
Input:    Everything from Steps 1–8 living inside
          the workbook — environment info, data sources,
          detection coverage, ingest health,
          silent-log status, critical asset monitoring
Output:   Living dashboard of their security posture
          at a glance
Have it:  Foundation exists — gets richer with
          every step that feeds it
Note:     This is the story of the engagement told
          visually. The moment that makes them refer
          the next client.
```

